    <h2>Careers at Z+</h2>
    <p>We are recruiting staff to deliver our services and maintain a high level of customer satisfaction.</p>
    <h3>Careers Consultant (full-time)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Role:</strong> Develops and delivers training courses and provides guidance to
        individuals. Duties include client interviews, advising on educational/employment options,
        organising training sessions/career forums, liaising with employers, giving talks,
        monitoring client progress, and one-to-one coaching.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Requirements:</strong> Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, creativity,
        resourcefulness, and ideally previous recruitment experience.
      </li>
      <li><strong>Employment Details:</strong> Full-time role with a salary range of £26,000–£30,000.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>To Apply:</strong> Send your CV and an explanation of why you wish to join Z+ to
        <a href="mailto:info@z-plus.co.uk">info@z-plus.co.uk</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Customer Success Intern (Administrative/Customer Service Intern)</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Role:</strong> Ensures UK students receive high-level customer service.
        Responsibilities include responding to customer feedback, identifying root causes of
        problems, providing solutions, collaborating with other departments to resolve issues,
        reporting high-risk concerns, and optimising operational processes.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Candidate Profile:</strong> Self-motivated, proactive, adept at discovering and
        solving problems, adaptable, with excellent communication and interpersonal skills. Must
        handle disputes professionally and prioritise customer service. Strong Chinese and English
        language skills are highly preferred.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Employment Details:</strong> Paid internship lasting 3–6 months, working 3–5 days
        per week in an offline/hybrid mode. The role is based in the City of London.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>To Apply:</strong> Send a CV and a brief summary explaining why you want to join Z+
        to <a href="mailto:info@z-plus.co.uk">info@z-plus.co.uk</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
